title: A1466 820-3437-B no power
message:
HI,

I have an A1466 820-3437-B with no power. It had liquid contact (a bit of coffee, not much), and i replaced the U1959, C1950 and R8167 that had a bit od corrosion,  but with no sucess. It had the J6100 with a lot of corrosion, and I have taked it out.
It has green light, but no fan spin, and it consumes 95 mA on PSU.

The SYS_PWROK_R test point is missing and don't know if it is essencial  (it had corrosion and disappeared when i cleaned with IPA), and i have 0V on SYS_PWROK_R.

Can you help?

title: A1466 820-3437-B no power
message:
You must check all SPI Bus Series Termination resisotrs and their traces.
Do you get any pulse on the coils?
Steady 3V3_S5/SUS?

title: A1466 820-3437-B no power
message: Do you have good trace between U1950 and R1962?

title: A1466 820-3437-B no power
message:
Yes, i do, but i have 0V on pin3 of U1950.
It seams that i don't have trace between R8166 and R8167. I'm going to replace R8167...

title: A1466 820-3437-B no power
message:
It worked. 
It seams that the R8167, besides it has the right resistance, had something wrong with it. After replacement it worked. 
Thanks!
